OL,7,FAt the conclusion of the non-jury
OL,8,Ftrial, Judge Smyth found both men
OL,9,Fguilty of two counts of the
OL,10,Fpreparation of terrorist acts, two
OL,11,Fcounts of possessing articles for use
OL,12,Fin terrorism and two counts of
OL,13,Fattempting to collect or make records
OL,14,Fof information likely to be useful to
OL,15,Fa person committing or preparing an
OL,16,Fact of terrorism.
OL,18,FDuring sentencing on Friday, Judge
OL,19,FSmyth described their offending as a
OL,20,F"persistent course of conduct carried
OL,21,Fout over a number of weeks."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/13
