OL,7,FRegarding Reynolds, the Judge said his
OL,8,Flong period on remand which did not
OL,9,Fresult in an admission of guilt,
OL,10,Fdespite overwhelming evidence, was a
OL,11,F"matter of considerable concern...
OL,12,Fthat can only demonstrate a continued
OL,13,Fcommitment to the commission of such
OL,14,Foffences."
OL,16,FDeeming both men to be dangerous
OL,17,Foffenders, Judge Smyth imposed the
OL,18,Fextended custodial sentences which she
OL,19,Fsaid were necessary to protect the
OL,20,Fpublic.
